text: <@U286Q175Y> I ran Adventurer's Guildhouse in Reki just for the lolz for awhile, and it was bad. If it tapped for colorless maybe but spending a land drop on a land that doesn't tap for mana actively hurt, and that was in a mono deck.
But if you don't count it in your land slot but more as an enchantment...
I usually dont count maze of ith, tabernacle, bazaar as land slots
I play urborg in kethis but still lol
Even if you don't count it though you have to use a landdrop to play it. That's maybe fine for something super impactful like Maze or Bazaar but it felt terrible for something trolly
Well maze is different in that you generally can sandbag it until you need it
Bazaar is pretty bad in most decks lol. Ive been wanting to write a series on high $ cards and what they are good for
I cannot stop thinking about Urza
Either want to just bite the bullet and build the What You Would expect urza or figure out what deck it goes in
Go real hipster and put him in C18 Saheeli.

I like the idea that Don is such a hipster deckbuilder that he starts by playing only off-the wall shit like Taniwha, but then that becomes too mainstream so now he comes full circle and hipsters his hipsterness and builds Atraxa and all the popular stuff
How many artifacts do you have?
Taniwhas not built right now. But usually a decent amount but most mana rocks
Sometimes w taniwha you are topdecking and need a mana outlet to get some random value out of the lands before you phase out

Also... ive learned a few tricks protecting niv mizzet i might put in w taniwha

[[string of disappearances]] and [[chain of vapor]] and [[Submerge]] most notably. Either clutch spot removal, or avoid commander tax (target your own dude) and often get some additional value out of it.
